recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Whereas structural changes have come about in the European organizations representing agricultural workers since the setting up of the Joint Committee and new needs have arisen because of the enlargement of the Community;
Whereas the Commission must take account of the situation in the individual Member States so as to ensure the participation of employers and employees in agriculture in the work of the Joint Committee and thus maintain the effective representation of all interested parties;
Whereas the presence at the Committee's meetings of observers from organizations other than those referred to in Article 4 of Commission Decision 74/442/EEC (1) may increase the Committee's effectiveness,
